5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.tiktok.com%2F%40mackmoan1988%2Fvideo%2F7301321729681394974%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eviral%20TikTok%20video%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMackenzie%20Moan%2C%20who%20goes%20by%20the%20handle%20%40mackmoan1988%20on%20TikTok%20and%20was%20interviewed%20by%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.foxbusiness.com%2Fvideo%2F6341796452112%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EFox%20Business%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20said%20she's%20a%20registered%20nurse%20and%20a%20full-time%20student%20with%20two%20children.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20feel%20like%20my%20husband%20and%20I%20are%20doing%20everything%20right.%20We%20both%20have%20good%20jobs%2C%20I'm%20a%20nurse%20...%20I%20work%20full-time%2C%20he%20works%20full-time%2C%26quot%3B%20Moan%20said%20in%20the%20TikTok%20video%20while%20sobbing.%20The%20video%20was%20uploaded%20on%20November%2014%20and%20has%20amassed%20over%201.5%20million%20views.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20explained%20that%20four%20days%20after%20she%20and%20her%20husband%20received%20their%20paychecks%20and%20had%20paid%20their%20bills%2C%20they%20were%20left%20with%20around%20%24200%20to%20%24300%20to%20spend%20over%2010%20days.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMoan%20emphasized%20that%20they%20live%20in%20a%20modest%20house%20with%20three%20bedrooms%20and%20a%20bathroom%2C%20and%20that%20both%20she%20and%20her%20partner%20make%20%26quot%3Bgood%20money%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3Bdon't%20live%20above%20our%20means.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BGrowing%20up%20we%20were%20told%20to%20get%20a%20degree%2C%20work%20to%20support%20your%20family%20%E2%80%A6%20here%20we%20are%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BI%20don't%20know%20what%20less%20than%20paycheck%20to%20paycheck%20is.%20What%20is%20that%3F%20Poverty%20%E2%80%A6%20as%20a%20registered%20nurse%2C%20with%20a%20husband%2C%20with%20a%20second%20income%3F%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSomebody%20has%20to%20do%20something%20to%20change%20this%2C%26quot%3B%20Moan%20said%20in%20an%20impassioned%20plea.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETikTok%20users%20are%20rallying%20in%20support%20of%20Moan%20and%20sharing%20similar%20struggles%20with%20one%20comment%20saying%3A%20%26quot%3BI%20promise%20it's%20not%20just%20you.%20It's%20all%20of%20America.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnother%20user%20wrote%3A%20%26quot%3BI%20make%206%20figures%20and%20am%20STILL%20paycheck%20to%20paycheck!%20%E2%80%A6%20I%20don't%20live%20beyond%20my%20means%20either.%20It%20is%20so%20depressing!%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBusiness%20Insider%20reached%20out%20to%20Moan%20for%20comment%20via%20TikTok%20but%20did%20not%20immediately%20hear%20back%20outside%20of%20regular%20working%20hours.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMoan's%20video%20reflects%20the%20struggle%20of%20many%20US%20workers.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAlthough%20wages%20finally%20caught%20up%20with%20inflation%20in%20May%20this%20year%2C%20the%20gap%20between%20buying%20power%20and%20inflation%20remains.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BHouseholds%20are%20seeing%20their%20finances%20stretched%20thinly%20by%20the%20combination%20of%20high%20prices%20for%20goods%20and%20services%20as%20well%20as%20high%20interest%20rates%2C%26quot%3B%20Brett%20House%2C%20an%20economics%20professor%20at%20Columbia%20Business%20School%2C%20previously%20told%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cnbc.com%2F2023%2F10%2F31%2F62percent-of-americans-still-live-paycheck-to-paycheck-amid-inflation.html%23%3A~%3Atext%3DPersonal%2520Finance-%2C62%2525%2520of%2520Americans%2520are%2520still%2520living%2520paycheck%2520to%2520paycheck%252C%2520making%2Cmain%2520financial%2520lifestyle%252C%2527%2520report%2520finds%26amp%3Btext%3DThe%2520number%2520of%2520Americans%2520who%2Cprices%2520and%2520higher%2520interest%2520rates.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ECNBC%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%26quot%3BMany%20are%20having%20to%20make%20tough%20choices%20to%20defer%20discretionary%20spending%20in%20order%20to%20stay%20on%20top%20of%20t