0Terminal%20on%20February%2024%2C%202023%20in%20Luganville%2C%20Vanuatu.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65648502fd6200867dcf762a%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223472%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EP%26amp%3BO's%20Pacific%20Adventure.%3Cp%3EMatt%20Blyth%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EP%26amp%3BO's%20Pacific%20Adventure%20was%20supposed%20to%20stop%20at%20multiple%20ports%20in%20New%20Zealand%2C%20The%20Guardian%20reported.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EBut%20it%20was%20turned%20away%20due%20to%20invasive%20species%20on%20the%20hull%2C%20and%20poor%20diving%20conditions%20stopped%20it%20being%20cleaned.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EPassengers%20have%20been%20suffering%20from%20sea%20sickness%2C%20and%20can%20receive%20a%20refund%20and%20%24200%20onboard%20credit%20after%20an%20outcry.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theguardian.com%2Faustralia-news%2F2023%2Fnov%2F27%2Fp-and-o-cruises-pacific-adventure-new-zealand-biohazard-standards-tasmania%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EPassengers%20on%20a%20P%26amp%3BO%20cruise%3C%2Fa%3E%20have%20been%20stuck%20onboard%20and%20suffering%20from%20sea%20sickness%20after%20the%20ship%20was%20turned%20away%20from%20New%20Zealand%2C%20The%20Guardian%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20cruise%20was%20supposed%20to%20stop%20at%20multiple%20ports%20in%20New%20Zealand%20after%20departing%20Sydney%20in%20Australia%20last%20Monday.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20Pacific%20Adventure%20was%20prevented%20from%20docking%20in%20New%20Zealand%2C%20which%20has%20strict%20biosecurity%20laws%2C%20due%20to%20invasive%20species%20attached%20to%20its%20hull%2C%20per%20The%20Guardian.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDivers%20were%20scheduled%20to%20remove%20three%20juvenile%20mussels%20and%20one%20Lace%20Coral%2C%20but%20diving%20conditions%20were%20worse%20than%20anticipated%2C%20The%20Guardian%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20a%20result%2C%20passengers%20have%20been%20left%20at%20sea%20for%20longer%20than%20expected.%20One%20passenger%2C%20Jake%20Welch%2C%20told%20The%20Guardian%3A%20%26quot%3BThe%20sick%20bags%20are%20quickly%20disappearing%20from%20the%20stairwells.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20cruise%20has%20been%20rescheduled%20to%20only%20stop%20at%20three%20ports%20in%20Australia%2C%20according%20to%20The%20Guardian.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMy%20wife%20and%20I%20are%20on%20this%20crummy%20cruise%20to%20nowhere%2C%20very%20disappointing%2C%20never%20travelling%20on%20P%26amp%3BO%20again%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20one%20passenger%20on%20a%20Facebook%20page%20created%20for%20the%20cruise.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWelch%20told%20The%20Guardian%20that%20P%26amp%3BO%20initially%20offered%20a%2050%25%20%26quot%3Bfuture%20cruise%20credit%26quot%3B%20scheme%20to%20passengers%2C%20which%20prompted%20an%20outcry.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20operator%20is%20now%20offering%20passengers%20a%20refund%20and%20%24200%20onboard%20credit%2C%20per%20The%20Guardian.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20have%20listened%20to%20the%20feedback%20from%20our%20guests%20and%20understand%20not%20all%20of%20them%20wish%20to%20cruise%20with%20us%20again%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20P%26amp%3BO%20spokesperson%20told%20the%20newspaper.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAgain%2C%20we%20apologise%20for%20the%20change%20in%20itinerary%2C%20and%20thank%20our%20guests%20for%20their%20patience%20and%20understanding.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EP%26amp%3BO%20Australia%20did%20not%20immediately%20respond%20to%20Business%20Insider's%20request%20for%20comment%2C%20sent%20outside%20local%20working%20hours.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcruise-passengers-left-on-cruise-to-nowhere-suffer-sea-sickness-2023-11%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1701088287000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65648c51fd6200867dcf79a3%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcruise-passengers-left-on-cruise-to-nowhere-suffer-sea-sickness-2023-11%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Passengers%20on%20P%26amp%3BO's%20Pacific%20Adventure%20were%20left%20at%20sea%20for%20longer%20than%20expected%20after%20being%20prevented%20from%20docking%20in%20New%20Zealand%2C%20leading%20to%20seasickness.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22psyme%40insider.com%20(Pete%20Syme)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A4%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcruise-passengers-left-on-cruise-to-nowhere-suffer-sea-sickness-2023-11%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Increased%20Misuse%20of%20Governors%20for%20Political%20Reasons%20Is%20Destructive%20for%20Democracy%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2018%2F05%2F21013004%2FIMG_3491.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20November%209%2C%20on%20the%20eve%20of%20the%20completion%20of%20a%20year%20in%20the%20office%20as%20Chief%20Justice%20of%20India%2C%20D.Y.%20Chandrachud%2C%20in%20an%20interview%2C%20mentioned%20that%20%E2%80%9Cwe%20should%20not%20reject%20constitutional%20morality%20because%20it%20may%20sometimes%20be%20in%20tension%20with%20existing%20social%20practices%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20introducing%20%E2%80%98The%20Draft%20Constitution%E2%80%99%20to%20the%20Constituent%20Assembly%20on%20November%204%2C%201948%2C%20B.R.%20Ambedkar%20highlighted%20the%20need%20to%20diffuse%20%E2%80%98constitutional%20morality%E2%80%99%20in%20Indian%20society.%20He%20opined%20that%20it%20is%20imperative%20to%20deepen%20the%20democracy%2C%20which%20is%20only%20a%20%E2%80%98top-dressing%20on%20Indian%20soil%2C%20which%20is%20essentially%20undemocratic%E2%80%99.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20journey%20of%2075%20years%20of%20constitutionalism%20in%20India%20provides%20the%20perfect%20context%20to%20revisit%20the%20idea%20of%20constitutional%20morality%20in%20light%20of%20the%20ongoing%20tussle%20between%20the%20governors%20and%20the%20elected%20governments%2C%20especially%20in%20Kerala%2C%20Maharashtra%2C%20Punjab%2C%20West%20Bengal%20and%20Tamil%20Nadu.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Supreme%20Court%20has%20expressed%20serious%20concerns%20about%20the%20delays%20by%20some%20of%20the%20governors%20in%20assenting%20to%20the%20Bills%20passed%20by%20the%20state%20legislatures.%20This%20violates%20the%20constitutional%20provisions%20and%20the%20doctrine%20of%20constitutional%20morality.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20constitution%20of%20India%20has%20envisaged%20the%20role%20of%20the%20governor%20as%20custodian%20of%20constitutionalism%20in%20the%20respective%20states%3B%20however%2C%20owing%20to%20the%20nature%20of%20appointment%20using%20nominee%2Fselection%20by%20the%20union%20government%2C%20most%20of%20the%20time%2C%20the%20governors%20abide%20by%20the%20obligation%20to%20the%20ruling%20dispensation%20rather%20than%20to%20the%20constitutionalism.%20This%20has%20deepened%20the%20crisis%20between%20the%20union%20and%20state%20relations%20by%20corroding%20the%20principle%20of%20cooperative%20federalism.%20The%20conduct%20of%20governor%2Fs%20in%20these%20states%20has%20resurrected%20the%20question%20of%20the%20need%20to%20continue%20the%20governor%E2%80%99s%20office%20in%20parliamentary%20democracy.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20inordinate%20delay%20of%20governor%2Fs%20in%20granting%20assent%20to%20the%20Bills%20has%20become%20the%20unwritten%20rule%20in%20some%20of%20these%20states%2C%20thereby%20diminishing%20the%20credibility%20of%20the%20institution%20of%20the%20governor.%20Misusing%20the%20governor%E2%80%99s%20office%20by%20the%20Union%20government%20in%20power%20is%20not%20entirely%20new.%20It%20has%20been%20in%20practice%20since%201950.%20This%20is%20true%20for%20the%20largest%20political%20alliances%20of%20NDA%20and%20UPA%2C%20led%20by%20the%20Bharatiya%20Janata%20Party%20and%20Indian%20National%20Congress%2C%20respectively.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20increased%20misuse%20of%20the%20governor%E2%80%99s%20office%20by%20the%20ruling%20governments%20for%20political%20reasons%20is%20the%20most%20destructive%20pattern%20in%20our%20democracy.%20The%20arbitrary%20use%20of%20Article%20356%20is%20one%20of%20the%20most%20commonly%20used%20political%20strategies%20through%20the%20governor%E2%80%99s%20office%20to%20dismantle%20the%20state-elected%20governments.%20Only%20the%20President%20of%20India%2C%20upon%20receiving%20a%20report%20from%20the%20governor%2C%20can%20proclaim%20an%20emergency%20in%20case%20of%20the%20state%E2%80%99s%20constitutional%20machinery%20failure.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EArticle%20356%20(1)%20of%20the%20constitution%20of%20India%20reads%2C%20%E2%80%9CIf%20the%20President%2C%20on%20receipt%20of%20a%20report%20from%20the%20Governor%20of%20the%20State%20or%20otherwise%2C%20is%20satisfied%20that%20a%20situation%20has%20arisen%20in%20which%20the%20government%20of%20the%20State%20cannot%20be%20carried%20on%20by%20following%20the%20provisions%20of%20this%20Constitution%E2%80%A6%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20word%20%E2%80%9Cotherwise%E2%80%9D%20in%20the%20provision%20mentioned%20above%20is%20left%20undefined%20and%20gives%20scope%20for%20the%20use%20or%20misuse%20of%20the%20powers%20by%20the%20constitutional%20authorities%20to%20regulate%20the%20states%E2%80%99%20acts.%20The%20original%20draft%20of%20the%20constitution%20did%20not%20contain%20the%20word%20%E2%80%9Cotherwise%E2%80%9D.%20It%20is%20worthwhile%20to%20recollect%20the%20Constituent%20Assembly%20debates%20on%20Article%20278%20and%20present%20Article%20356.%20Article%20356%20of%20the%20constitution%20must%20be%20seen%20in%20conjunction%20with%20Articles%20352-359%20and%20360%20(financial%20emergency)%20and%20not%20alone.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Constituent%20Assembly%20was%20unhappy%20with%20this%20Article%2C%20especially%20H.V.%20Kamath%2C%20who%20objected%20to%20the%20word%20%E2%80%9Cotherwise%E2%80%9D%20in%20the%20provision%20and%20moved%20an%20amendment%20to%20delete%20the%20word.%20He%20observed%20that%20if%20the%20amendment%20was%20not%20accepted%2C%20%E2%80%9Cwe%20are%20laying%20ourselves%20open%20to%20snare%20traps%20in%20our%20path%20wherein%20we%20shall%20be%20caught%20beyond%20any%20rescue%E2%80%9D.%20The%20current%20tactic%20of%20delay%20in%20assenting%20the%20Bills%2Flaws%20passed%20by%20the%20state%20governments%20by%20some%20governors%20is%20another%20arm%20to%20suppress%20democracy%20and%20the%20state%E2%80%99s%20sovereignty.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20fact%20that%20there%20is%20a%20conflict%20between%20the%20governor%E2%80%99s%20offices%20and%20the%20elected%20governments%20is%20sad.%20The%20immediate%20consequences%20of%20this%20trend%20are%20(i)%20affects%20public%20governance%20and%20administration%20(ii)%20erodes%20the%20harmonious%20relationship%20between%20the%20state%20and%20the%20Governor%E2%80%99s%20office%20(iii)%20destabilises%20the%20elected%20governments%20as%20they%20are%20under%20pressure%20of%20non-performing%20governance%20(iv)%20corrodes%20the%20union-state%20relations.%20Overall%2C%20the%20federal%20scheme%20of%20the%20constitution%20is%20in%20a%20state%20of%20disequilibrium.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ESolutions%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGiven%20this%20precarious%20situation%20where%20even%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20has%20raised%20questions%20on%20the%20conduct%20of%20Governors%20in%20clearing%20the%20Bills%2Flaws%2C%20the%20following%20steps%20are%20necessary%20to%20come%20out%20of%20this%20governance%20conundrum.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFirstly%2C%20the%20state%20government%20must%20be%20consulted%20before%20the%20governor%E2%80%99s%20appointment%20by%20the%20Union%20government%2C%20as%20recommended%20by%20the%20Sarkaria%20Commission.%20This%20will%20ensure%20the%20much-needed%20consultation%20between%20the%20union%20and%20state%20governments%2C%20thereby%20strengthening%20the%20relationship%20between%20both%20of%20these%20governments%20in%20the%20true%20spirit%20of%20cooperative%20federalism.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESecondly%2C%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20of%20India%20must%20direct%20the%20Union%20Ministry%20of%20Law%20and%20Justice%20to%20frame%20the%20guidelines%20for%20the%20governor%E2%80%99s%20office%2C%20in%20consultation%20with%20the%20Law%20Commission%20of%20India%2C%20to%20assent%20to%20the%20Bills%20on%20time%20to%20avoid%20unregulated%20delays%20in%20future.%20Thirdly%2C%20empower%20the%20office%20of%20the%20President%20of%20India%20to%20recall%20the%20governor%2Fs%20who%20are%20the%20subject%20of%20a%20constitutional%20violation%20in%20discharging%20the%20duties%20as%20per%20Article%20200.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELastly%2C%20the%20time%20has%20come%20to%20remove%20the%20word%20%E2%80%9Cotherwise%E2%80%9D%20in%20Article%20356%20through%20a%20constitutional%20amendment%2C%20as%20governors%20have%20misused%20the%20word%20to%20dissolve%20many%20elected%20governments%20in%20states.%20This%20will%20curtail%20some%20of%20the%20discretionary%20powers%20(different%20from%20those%20accrued%20under%20the%20Fifth%20and%20Sixth%20Schedule%20of%20the%20Constitution)%20and%20prevent%20the%20misuse%20of%20the%20Governor%E2%80%99s%20office%20by%20the%20union%20government%20in%20power.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3ENayakara%20Veeresha%20is%20an%20independent%20researcher%20and%20writer%20on%20governance%20and%20development.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.deccanherald.com%2Fopinion%2Fgoverning-the-governors-2785777%5C%22%3Earticle%3C%2Fa%3E%20was%20originally%20published%20by%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.deccanherald.com%2F%5C%22%3EDeccan%20Herald%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1701088249000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2018%2F05%2F21013004%2FIMG_3491.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fmisuse-governors-political-reasons-destructive-democracy%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20Supreme%20Court%20must%20direct%20the%20Unio