0CODA%20recently%20gained%20popularity%20as%20a%20film%20of%20the%20same%20name%20made%20a%20big%20splash%20at%20the%20Academy%20Awards%20in%202022.%20In%20India%2C%20the%201996%20film%20%E2%80%98Khamoshi%20%E2%80%93%20The%20Musical%E2%80%99%20was%20among%20the%20first%20to%20portray%20the%20plight%20of%20the%20Deaf%20community%20as%20authentically%20as%20possible.%20From%20bringing%20forth%20the%20seclusion%20experienced%20by%20CODAs%20to%20highlighting%20the%20numerous%20barriers%20for%20Deaf%20communities%2C%20Sanjay%20Leela%20Bhansali%E2%80%99s%20directorial%20debut%20was%20well%20ahead%20of%20its%20time.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20an%20attempt%20to%20become%20their%20parents%E2%80%99%20voice%2C%20CODAs%20grow%20up%20a%20little%20too%20quickly%2C%20often%20shedding%20innocence%20and%20befriending%20maturity%20at%20a%20tender%20age.%20These%20children%20form%20the%20bridge%20between%20the%20Deaf%20and%20hearing%20worlds.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20article%20aims%20to%20shed%20light%20on%20these%20young%20people%20doing%20incredible%20work%20for%20their%20loved%20ones%20and%20bring%20forward%20their%20lives%2C%20issues%2C%20and%20stories%20in%20everyday%20parlance.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%201200px)%20100vw%2C%201200px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2Ffacts-about-sign-language-1-1-1700576918.png%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2Ffacts-about-sign-language-1-1-1700576918.png%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2Ffacts-about-sign-language-1-1-1700576918-300x162.png%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2Ffacts-about-sign-language-1-1-1700576918-500x269.png%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2Ffacts-about-sign-language-1-1-1700576918-768x413.png%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2Ffacts-about-sign-language-1-1-1700576918-150x81.png%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-334627%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22646%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bid.org.uk%2Flatest-news%2Flatest-news%2Fpost%2F264-7-facts-about-sign-language%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EFollow%20this%20link%20to%20know%20more.%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EThrough%20their%20own%20words%C2%A0%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESarah%20explains%2C%20%E2%80%9CI%20have%20been%20my%20parents%E2%80%99%20interpreter%20throughout%20my%20life.%20Despite%20my%20undertaking%20a%20professional%20course%20with%20the%20Indian%20Sign%20Language%20Research%20and%20Training%20Centre%2C%20I%E2%80%99ve%20been%20signing%20for%20as%20long%20as%20I%20can%20remember!%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESurbhi%20Taneja%2C%20another%20CODA%2C%20has%20been%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F262492%2Fbaba-sidhaye-yashwant-prabhakar-deaf-mute-india-cricket-legend-runs%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eformally%20interpreting%3C%2Fa%3E%20since%20the%20age%20of%2010.%20%E2%80%9CI%20was%20interpreting%20at%20conferences%2C%20trying%20to%20make%20sense%20of%20the%20complex%20language%20that%20I%20did%20not%20understand%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20said.%20Surbhi%20is%20also%20a%20professional%20make-up%20artist.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CAt%20that%20time%2C%20sign%20language%20interpretation%20was%20not%20a%20formal%20profession%20so%20one%20could%20easily%20find%20CODAs%20interpreting%20in%20formal%20settings.%20It%20is%20often%20assumed%20that%20all%20CODAs%20are%20more%20likely%20to%20take%20up%20sign%20language%20interpretation%20as%20a%20profession%20but%20that%20is%20not%20true.%20The%20choice%20lies%20with%20the%20person%20and%20that%20is%20also%20one%20of%20the%20aspects%20we%20work%20on%2C%E2%80%9D%20Surbhi%20shares.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShe%20is%20the%20founder%20of%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.facebook.com%2Fcodaindia%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ECODA%20India%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20community%20that%20aims%20to%20foster%20a%20sense%20of%20identity%20among%20CODAs%20and%20solidarity.%20%E2%80%9CThe%20Deaf%20community%20is%20very%20isolated%20and%20people%20feel%20that%20they%E2%80%99re%20alone%20in%20their%20journey.%20So%2C%20CODA%20India%20assists%20people%2C%20especially%20K%2FCODAs%20(Kid%20CODAs%20%E2%80%93%C2%A0CODAs%20younger%20than%2018%20years%20of%20age)%20to%20find%20their%20identities%20and%20take%20pride%20in%20them.%E2%80%9D%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CSince%20the%20child%20is%20hearing%20(able%20to%20hear)%20and%20often%20interprets%20for%20their%20Deaf%20parents%2C%20there%E2%80%99s%20a%20lot%20of%20responsibility%20that%20is%20shouldered%20on%20them.%20This%20leads%20to%20the%20D%2Fdeaf%20person%20feeling%20disempowered.%20So%20we%20counsel%20them%20towards%20being%20the%20adult%20and%20taking%20responsibility%20for%20the%20child%2C%E2%80%9D%20Surbhi%20adds.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOftentimes%2C%20family%20members%20of%20Deaf%20adults%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F146728%2Fhearing-glasses-google-transcribe-deaf-delhi-madhav-lavakare%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edon%E2%80%99t%20know%20sign%20language%3C%2Fa%3E%20so%20their%20communication%20with%20them%20remains%20largely%20restricted%20to%20pleasantries.%20%E2%80%9CWhenever%20our%20relatives%20visit%20us%2C%20they%20only%20ask%20my%20parents%20whether%20or%20not%20they%20had%20food%20because%20that%20is%20easy%20to%20convey%20even%20if%20one%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20know%20sign%20language%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20says.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOver%20time%2C%20the%20conversations%20reduce%20and%20the%20bonds%20fade%20away.%20However%2C%20Sarah%20shares%20that%20now%20her%20family%20members%20try%20to%20learn%20the%20signs%20for%20a%20few%20words%20whenever%20they%20get%20a%20chance.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20India%2C%20there%20are%20only%20250%20sign%20language%20interpreters.%20There%20exists%20a%20wide%20gap%20between%20demand%20and%20supply.%20Even%20though%20CODAs%20have%20been%20signing%20for%20the%20longest%20time%2C%20they%20need%20a%20nine-month%20diploma%20in%20sign%20language%20training%20to%20be%20deemed%20professionals.%20There%20is%20a%20serious%20need%20for%20the%20government%20to%20incentivise%20sign%20language%20interpretation%20so%20that%20it%20is%20seen%20as%20a%20lucrative%20profession%20by%20others.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20general%20lack%20of%20awareness%20about%20the%20Deaf%20community%20tends%20to%20make%20people%20assume%20that%20the%20interpreter%20is%20conveying%20their%20own%20thoughts%20and%20not%20the%20D%2Fdeaf%20person%E2%80%99s.%20%E2%80%9CThis%20is%20something%20that%20comes%20up%20quite%20often.%20People%20get%20offended%20when%20I%20shout%20or%20express%20anger%20or%20interpret%20something%20offensive%20on%20the%20Deaf%20person%E2%80%99s%20behalf.%20I%E2%80%99m%20just%20doing%20my%20job%2C%E2%80%9D%20Sarah%20highlights.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20won%E2%80%99t%20be%20wrong%20to%20say%20that%20Sarah%20has%20been%20a%20constant%20for%20her%20parents%2C%20which%20is%20reflected%20in%20the%20bonds%20they%20share.%20Ever%20since%20she%20was%20a%20child%2C%20be%20it%20for%20doctor%E2%80%99s%20appointments%20or%20family%20gatherings%2C%20Sarah%20has%20been%20accompanying%20her%20parents%20everywhere%20as%20their%20interpreter.%20While%20it%20has%20helped%20foster%20a%20stronger%20and%20more%20open%20bond%20with%20her%20parents%2C%20%E2%80%98age-inappropriate%E2%80%99%20interpretation%20can%20also%20sometimes%20lead%20to%20the%20%3Ca%2