rly%2C%20D%2Fdeaf%20persons%20and%20CODAs%20grow%20up%20among%20others%20with%20similar%20or%20shared%20experiences.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESarah%2C%20whose%20initial%20interaction%20with%20life%20was%20only%20through%20the%20lens%20of%20her%20parents%E2%80%99%2C%20felt%20at%20odds%20with%20others.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIt%20was%20quite%20absurd%20for%20hearing%20people%20that%20I%20had%20Deaf%20parents%20or%20that%20we%20used%20sign%20language%20to%20communicate.%20But%20for%20me%2C%20it%20was%20the%20most%20normal%20thing%20ever%20because%20that%E2%80%99s%20how%20we%E2%80%99ve%20always%20been.%20Once%20when%20someone%20sympathised%20with%20me%20I%20told%20them%2C%20%E2%80%98%3Cem%3EParents%20toh%20sabke%20Deaf%20hote%20hain%E2%80%99%3C%2Fem%3E%20(Everyone%E2%80%99s%20parents%20are%20Deaf)%20I%20realised%20much%20later%20that%20that%20is%20not%20the%20case!%E2%80%9D%20Sarah%20says.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESurbhi%2C%20however%2C%20grew%20up%20in%20a%20joint%20family.%20%E2%80%9CThe%20hearing%20family%20members%20often%20tell%20CODAs%20that%20their%20parents%20are%20good%20for%20nothing.%20After%20listening%20to%20such%20remarks%2C%20how%20will%20the%20child%20come%20to%20accept%20their%20parent%E2%80%99s%20identity%20and%20their%20own%20relationship%20with%20the%20community%3F%E2%80%9D%20she%20shares.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CNo%20one%20really%20told%20me%20that%20it%20was%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F117179%2Fmartial-arts-deaf-children-instructor-sign-language%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eokay%20to%20have%20Deaf%20parents%3C%2Fa%3E.%20There%20was%20a%20staunch%20stigma%20and%20people%20saw%20it%20as%20a%20matter%20of%20shame.%20So%2C%20it%20was%20difficult%20for%20me%20to%20accept%20their%20identity%20and%20be%20open%20about%20it.%20However%2C%20as%20I%20grew%20up%2C%20I%20knew%20that%20it%20was%20not%20their%20fault%20that%20they%20were%20Deaf.%20Eventually%2C%20I%20opened%20up%20and%20asked%20my%20parents%20to%20accompany%20me%20to%20PTMs%20in%20school%2C%E2%80%9D%20Surbhi%20adds.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20Indian%20community%2C%20there%E2%80%99s%20a%20lot%20of%20emphasis%20on%20getting%20rid%20of%20one%E2%80%99s%20disability%20or%20hiding%20it.%20It%20is%20believed%20that%20people%20with%20disabilities%20are%20unhappy%20with%20their%20lives.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20Sarah%2C%20there%20were%20times%20when%20random%20strangers%20came%20up%20to%20them%20in%20public%20places%20and%20offered%20unsolicited%20pieces%20of%20advice%20to%20her%20parents%20such%20as%20using%20a%20variety%20of%20oils%20to%20get%20their%20hearing%20back.%20This%20is%20not%20only%20a%20breach%20of%20the%20person%E2%80%99s%20privacy%20and%20personal%20space%20but%20also%20disrespectful%20to%20their%20identity%20as%20a%20disabled%20person.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESeveral%20myths%20like%20these%20go%20around%20spreading%20misinformation%20about%20the%20Deaf%20community.%20%E2%80%9CNot%20only%20the%20Deaf%20community%2C%20but%20there%E2%80%99s%20also%20a%20lot%20of%20stigma%20around%20CODAs%20too%2C%20as%20most%20of%20us%20struggle%20with%20getting%20admission%20in%20schools%20because%20teachers%20feel%20that%20our%20parents%20would%20not%20be%20able%20to%20teach%20us%2C%20and%20that%20would%20lower%20the%20school%E2%80%99s%20result%2C%E2%80%9D%20Surbhi%20highlights.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndia%20occupies%20the%20first%20position%20among%20countries%20in%20South%20Asia%20in%20terms%20of%20size.%20This%20means%20that%20the%20number%20of%20people%20living%20with%20Deafness%20would%20also%20be%20the%20most.%20However%2C%20the%20data%20is%20not%20very%20clear%20on%20that.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20National%20Association%20of%20the%20Deaf%20reveals%20that%20around%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Fnadindia.org%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E18%20million%20people%3C%2Fa%3E%20are%20Deaf%2C%20the%20Indian%20Journal%20of%20Otology%20estimates%20that%20close%20to%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.indianjotol.org%2Farticle.asp%3Fissn%3D0971-7749%3Byear%3D2016%3Bvolume%3D22%3Bissue%3D2%3Bspage%3D73%3Bepage%3D76%3Baulast%3DVarshney%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E63%20million%20people%3C%2Fa%3E%20are%20either%20D%2Fdeaf%20or%20hard%20of%20hearing.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDespite%20such%20large%20numbers%2C%20awareness%20about%20the%20disability%20is%20barely%20enough.%20It%20is%20not%20surprising%20that%2C%20at%20the%20onset%20of%20the%20pandemic%2C%20the%20community%20was%20pushed%20further%20to%20the%20periphery%20of%20society%20as%20many%20were%20unaware%20of%20what%20was%20happening.%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov%2Fpmc%2Farticles%2FPMC8117910%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ECommunication%20challenges%20exacerbated%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20the%20community%20were%20already%20scarce%20as%20people%20wore%20face%20masks%2C%20practised%20social%20distancing%2C%20and%20met%20via%20virtual%20meetings.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20it%20is%20important%20to%20be%20aware%20and%20inclusive%2C%20one%20must%20also%20respect%20individual%20preferences%20and%20use%20communication%20styles%20that%20suit%20the%20needs%20of%20D%2Fdeaf%20people.%20Due%20to%20the%20missing%20numbers%2C%20the%20challenges%20D%2Fdeaf%20people%20experience%20get%20exacerbated%20which%20further%20pushes%20them%20to%20the%20peripheries%20of%20society.%20It%20is%20about%20time%20that%20we%20work%20on%20ourselves%2C%20become%20Deaf-aware%2C%20and%20foster%20an%20inclusive%20society.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EWritten%20by%20V-shesh%3B%20Edited%20by%20Padmashree%20Pande.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1700577333000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2Fdeaf-and-Deaf.jpg-1700576818.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F%3Fp%3D334578%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22With%20the%20Indian%20Sign%20Language%20(ISL)%20being%20their%20only%20tongue%20to%20communicate%20in%20with%20their%20parents%2C%20these%20CODAs%2C%20or%20Children%20of%20Deaf%20Adults%2C%20share%20what%20it%20is%20like%20to%20live%20a%20day%20in%20their%20lives.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22Guest%20Contributor%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A1%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F334578%2Fcoda-child-of-deaf-adult-indian-sign-language-isl%2F%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Why%20This%20JEE%20Topper%20Chose%20to%20Launch%20a%20Startup%20Over%20Accepting%20IIT-B%E2%80%99s%20Placement%20Packages%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20night%20before%20the%20JEE%20Mains%20exam%20I%20was%20nervous.%20I%20remember%20calling%20my%20professor%20anxiously.%20He%20said%20to%20me%2C%20%E2%80%98Sachin%20Tendulkar%20is%20a%20great%20player.%20But%20even%20if%20he%20fails%20to%20score%20a%20century%20in%20one%20match%2C%20he%20knows%20he%20will%20in%20the%20next%20one.%20He%20trusts%20his%20abilities%20more%20than%20circumstances.%E2%80%99%20The%20day%20of%20the%20exam%20dawned.%20Ninety%20questions%20stared%20at%20me.%20I%20had%20one%20attempt%20and%20I%20had%20to%20make%20it%20count.%20After%201.5%20hours%20of%20solving%20questions%2C%20I%20looked%20to%20see%20how%20far%20I%E2%80%99d%20gotten.%20I%E2%80%99d%20only%20managed%20to%20attempt%2030.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20Kalpit%20Veerwal%20%E2%80%94%20famous%20for%20scoring%20a%20perfect%20360%2F360%20in%20the%20JEE%20Mains%202017%20exam%20%E2%80%94%20recalls%20that%20moment%20in%20time%2C%20he%20terms%20it%20%E2%80%9C%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F334155%2Fbengaluru-ngo-dream-a-dream-educates-underprivileged-children-life-skills-h